{"title_page": "Trafford Park Line", "text_new": "{{short description|A light rail line on the Manchester Metrolink network in Greater Manchester, England}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox rail line\n|box_width       =\n|name            = Trafford Park Line\n|color           = ffdb4e\n|logo            =\n|logo_width      =\n|logo_alt        =\n|image           = Start of Trafford Line at Pomona.JPG\n|image_width     =\n|image_alt       =\n|caption         = Junction with the [[Eccles Line]] at the south end of [[Pomona tram stop]]\n|type            = [[Tram]]/[[Light rail]]\n|system          = [[Manchester Metrolink]]\n|status          = \n|locale          = [[Manchester]]<br>[[Trafford]]\n|start           = [[Cornbrook]]\n|end             = [[Intu Trafford Centre tram stop|Intu Trafford Centre]]\n|stations        = 6\n|routes          =\n|ridership2      =\n|open            = 22 March 2020\n|close           =\n|owner           =\n|operator        =\n|character       = [[Reserved track]] &<br>limited [[street running]]\n|depot           =\n|stock           = [[Bombardier M5000]]\n|linelength_km   = 5.5\n|linelength_mi   = 3.4\n|tracklength     = \n|tracks          =\n|gauge           = {{Railgauge|1435mm|allk=on}}\n|minradius       =\n|racksystem      =\n|routenumber     =\n|linenumber      =\n|electrification = 750 volts [[Direct current|DC]] overhead\n|speed_km/h      =\n|speed_mph       =\n|speed           =\n|elevation_m     =\n|elevation_ft    =\n|elevation       =\n|website         = [https://www.tfgm.com/trafford-park-line Transport for Greater Manchester]\n|map             = {{Manchester Trafford Centre Metrolink line}}\n|map_state       = collapsed}}\n\nThe '''Trafford Park Line''' is a [[light rail]] line on the [[Manchester Metrolink]] network in [[Greater Manchester]], England, running from [[Pomona tram stop|Pomona]] to the [[Intu Trafford Centre tram stop|Intu Trafford Centre]]. Its name derives from [[Trafford Park]], an area of the [[Metropolitan Borough of Trafford]], and the first planned [[industrial estate]] in the world.{{sfnp|Nicholls|1996|p=xiii|ps=}} The line opened in March 2020.\n\n==History==\nBetween July and September 2014, [[Transport for Greater Manchester]] (TfGM) conducted a public consultation to build the line.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.railtechnologymagazine.com/Rail-News/consultation-on-manchester-metrolink-extension-set-to-begin-|title=Consultation on Manchester Metrolink extension set to begin]|publisher=Rail Technology Magazine|date=16 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-manchester-28154179|title=Trafford Centre Metrolink plans to be discussed|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=7 July 2014}}</ref> In November 2014, TfGM applied for power under the [[Transport and Works Act 1992]] to build and operate the line.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tfgm.com/Corporate/Consultations/Metrolink-Trafford-Park-Line/Pages/Trafford-Park-Line.aspx|title= Trafford Park Line|work= Transport for Greater Manchester|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314202815/http://www.tfgm.com/Corporate/Consultations/Metrolink-Trafford-Park-Line/Pages/Trafford-Park-Line.aspx|archivedate=14 March 2016}}</ref> In October 2016, power to build the line was granted by the [[Secretary of State for Transport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-manchester-37645935|title=Metrolink's Trafford Park \u00a3350m Tramline Approved]|publisher=BBC News|date=13 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrolink.co.uk/pages/news.aspx?newsID=388|title=Green light for new Trafford Park Metrolink line|publisher=Metrolink|date=14 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/metrolink-trafford-centre-line-approved-12021610|title=Metrolink line to the Trafford Centre will go ahead despite objections from Coronation Street and Manchester United]|publisher=[[Manchester Evening News]]|date=14 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.railwaygazette.com/news/news/europe/single-view/view/powers-granted-for-manchester-metrolink-trafford-park-extension.html|title=Powers granted for Manchester Metrolink Trafford Park extension|publisher=[[Railway Gazette International]]|date=14 October 2016}}</ref> Construction commenced in January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ground broken on Manchester\u2019s Trafford Park Line|url=https://www.globalrailnews.com/2017/01/13/ground-broken-on-manchesters-trafford-park-line/|publisher=Global Rail News|accessdate=15 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/route-new-tram-line-trafford-14889695|title=This is the route new tram line to the Trafford Centre will take|first=Alexandra|last=Rucki|date=10 July 2018|website=[[Manchester Evening News]]}}</ref>\n\nThe final stretch of track was laid in November 2019, with the first test trams running soon after. The line opened on 22 March 2020, eight months earlier than originally planned,<ref>{{cite web |title=Metrolink's Trafford Park \u00a3350m tramline opening date revealed |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-manchester-51801265 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/people-greater-manchester-urged-not-17957387|title=People in Greater Manchester urged not to use public transport for anything other than \u2018essential journeys, with services to be \u2018stepped down\u2019 from Sunday|publisher=[[Manchester Evening News]]|date=21 March 2020}}</ref> despite suggestions that it might be delayed<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.placenorthwest.co.uk/news/metrolinks-trafford-park-line-to-open-as-planned-at-weekend/|title=Metrolink\u2019s Trafford Park line to open as planned at weekend|date=20 March 2020|work=Place North West}}</ref> as part of a review of all Metrolink services because of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320111325/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/trafford-park-tram-line-opening-17951741|publisher=[[Manchester Evening News]]|author=Charlotte Cox|title=Trafford Park tram line opening in doubt as Metrolink bosses hold crunch talks about network reductions|date=19 March 2020|accessdate=20 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320111325/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/trafford-park-tram-line-opening-17951741|archivedate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Route description==\nThe line branches off from the [[Eccles Line]] immediately south of [[Pomona tram stop|Pomona]], where provision was made for a future junction at the south\u2013western end when the viaduct on which it sits was built in the late 1990s. Stops have been built at [[Wharfside tram stop|Wharfside]], [[Imperial War Museum tram stop|Imperial War Museum]], [[Village tram stop|Village]], [[Parkway tram stop|Parkway]], [[Barton Dock Road tram stop|Barton Dock Road]] and the Trafford Centre. Future provision has been made to extend the line to [[Port Salford tram stop|Port Salford]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tfgm.com/journey_planning/Documents/PDFMaps/Met-FUTURE-PS-GEO.pdf|title=Metrolink future network|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203221337/http://www.tfgm.com/journey_planning/Documents/PDFMaps/Met-FUTURE-PS-GEO.pdf |archivedate=3 December 2013|publisher=[[Transport for Greater Manchester|TfGM]]}}</ref>\n\nServices initially operate as a self-contained shuttle between [[Cornbrook tram stop|Cornbrook]] and [[Intu Trafford Centre tram stop|Intu Trafford Centre]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.tfgm.com/news/trafford-park-line-launch-date-confirmed|title=Trafford Park Line opening date announced|publisher=[[Transport for Greater Manchester]]|date=9 March 2020|accessdate=14 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314152117/https://news.tfgm.com/news/trafford-park-line-launch-date-confirmed|archivedate=14 March 2020}}</ref> Eventually they are due to be extended to operate to [[Crumpsall tram stop|Crumpsall]] on the [[Bury Line]] by the end of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://beta.tfgm.com/travel-updates/crumpsall-works|title=Works at Crumpsall Metrolink stop|last=|first=|date=|website=TfGM|access-date=8 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/new-trafford-park-line-april-17450443|title=The Trafford Centre Metrolink line will open months earlier than expected|publisher=Manchester Evening News|date=20 December 2019}}</ref> \n\n==Rolling stock==\nTo provide rolling stock for the line and other service expansions, 27 [[Bombardier M5000]] trams were ordered; these will incorporate modifications to the existing fleet including new touch screen Vecom units for drivers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tfgm.com/press-release/contract-signed-for-27-new-trams|title=27 new trams on the way for Metrolink|website=Transport for Greater Manchester}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.railjournal.com/rolling-stock/manchester-orders-27-lrvs-to-boost-metrolink-capacity/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322021056/https://www.railjournal.com/rolling-stock/manchester-orders-27-lrvs-to-boost-metrolink-capacity/|archivedate=22 March 2020|title=Manchester orders 27 LRVs to boost Metrolink capacity|publisher=[[International Railway Journal]]|date=3 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline|Manchester Metrolink Trafford Park Line}}\n*{{Official|https://www.tfgm.com/trafford-park-line}}\n\n{{Manchester Metrolink tram stops}}\n\n[[Category:Manchester Metrolink lines]]\n[[Category:Railway lines opened in 2020]]\n[[Category:Trafford]]\n[[Category:2020 establishments in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|A light rail line on the Manchester Metrolink network in G